{"type":"message","id":"4fa85dc9","parentId":"69bb4361","timestamp":"2026-05-10T09:05:56.274Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing test files setup**\n\nI’ve planned some test files like `auth.test.ts`, `project-scope.test.ts`, and `app-flow.test.tsx`, and I'm considering using Vitest with React Testing Library. I need to make sure the project has no dependencies. Should T01 set up the test runner and contracts with failing tests? If the execution task isn’t complete, it needs to pass. I guess if T01 writes failing tests, it won’t pass unless the implementation is done in the same task.","thinkingSignature":"think-tag"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5nHEQyiX72A3Zc92yK35k3O7","name":"gsd_decision_save","arguments":{"choice":"Use an npm workspace monorepo with a TypeScript Fastify API (`apps/api`) and a Vite React Web UI (`apps/web`) for M001 local foundation work.","decision":"Select the local application structure for the authenticated web foundation.","made_by":"agent","rationale":"The repository currently only has a README, so S01 needs a small runnable skeleton. Fastify gives a lightweight backend with explicit middleware/hooks for auth and project permission checks, while Vite React provides a modern non-Streamlit product UI that can be tested locally without Next.js deployment complexity. npm workspaces keep Web, API, and future CLI packages in one local install path.","revisable":"Yes","scope":"architecture","when_context":"M001/S01 planning"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-openai","model":"gpt-5.5","usage":{"input":13732,"output":1205,"cacheRead":27136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42073,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778403938380}}
